div.p:
Whether when God hath by Faith purified the hearts of a people walking in Chriſtian brotherhood and fellowſhip together, hath he not Sanctified them? And in caſe any perſon ſhall now despiſe or decline their fellowſhip as unholy, doth he not ſinne againſt that Heavenly admonition delivered by ſpeciall Revelation unto Peter;
                  Act. 10.15. 
                  What God hath cleanſed (i. e. Purified or Sanctified) call not thou (or make not thou) common? Or can a man lightly call, or make that common, which God hath ſanctified in a more opprebrious and contumelious way, then by flying from it as polluted or unholy?
